0.01). The survival of patients of the Child's A or Child's B status was better 
than that of those with Child's C disease. Recurrence occurred in areas within 
the liver different from the original lesion in 34% in one year, 61% in two 
years and 66% in three years after PEI. PEI was then repeated in 61% of such 
patients.

