Oesophageal varices: prophylactic treatment?

Zeijen RN(1), Flendrig JA, van Spreeuwel JP.

Author information:
(1)Vakgroep Interne Geneeskunde, Academisch Ziekenhuis Maastricht.

Oesophageal varices: prophylactic treatment? Patients with oesophageal varices 
as a result of liver cirrhosis are at risk of bleeding from these varices. 
Because of the high mortality, specially from the first variceal haemorrhage, it 
would seem justified to pose the question: does prophylactic treatment of 
oesophageal varices reduce the risk of bleeding and improve life expectancy? A 
review of the literature shows that until now no mode of prophylactic therapy 
has succeeded in accomplishing these goals. It is not, therefore, possible at 
this time to advise the use of prophylactic treatment of oesophageal varices as 
a routine therapy.

